{
  "texts": [
    "In supervised NLP tasks, ELMO embeddings can be directly appended to the word vector input of task-specific models or their highest-level representations.",
    "Autoencoders are a type of unsupervised learning neural network model used for feature extraction and reconstruction of data.",
    "They work by compressing input data into a lowerdimensional encoding space and then attempting to reconstruct the input data from this encoding space, with the goal of learning useful features present in the data.",
    "An autoencoder consists of two parts: the encoder and the decoder.",
    "The encoder maps the input data to a lower-dimensional encoding representation, also known as the latent representation."
  ]
}